-- Sandoval, Executives Seek 150 Million Reais From BTG, Veja Says
-- B y   K a r e n   E e u w e n s
-- 2012-07-22T12:36:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-22/sandoval-executives-seek-150-million-reais-from-btg-veja-says.html
Grupo  Silvio Santos ’ former chief
executive officer Luiz Sandoval and former executives of Banco
Panamericano SA are seeking 150 million reais ($74 million) of
workers’ compensation from Banco BTG Pactual SA, Veja magazine
columnist Lauro Jardim reported, without saying where he got the
information.  BTG’s investor relations department didn’t immediately
respond, outside regular business hours, to a phone call and an
e-mail from Bloomberg News seeking comment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Karen Eeuwens in London at 
 keeuwens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dick Schumacher at 
 dschumacher@bloomberg.net  